cted to create a full game design document and, cooperating with others, a game (demo).", "et": "Kursus annab põhiteadmised, mis on vajalikud populaarsete arvuti/videomängude loomiseks, sh mängude kavandamine, disain, psühholoogia, graafika, turustamine, projektijuhtimine. Kursuse käigus loob õppija mängukavandi ning koost teiste liikmetega ka arvutimängu."}, "objectives": [{"en": "Provide the learner a structured knowledge of developing videogames and the steps required to do this, including game design, game psychology and marketing, with the general goal of teaching learners how to make successful videogames.", "et": "Anda õppijale struktureeritud ülevaade arvutimängude loomisest ja selle etappidest, sh mängudisainist ehk mängu kavandamisest, mängupsühholoogiast ja mängude turundamisest, täita eeldused edukate arvutimängude loomiseks."}], "learning_outcomes": [{"en": "The learner who has completed the course knows all main elements of developing video games (including gaming psychology, game analysis and marketing), skills to create practical game design documents from ideas and start projects to make them real. The learner is expected to create a complete design document and also (collaborating with a team formed with other learners) a computer game (demo).The learners will receive help from the university and lector for organizing the developing teams, finding partners and marketing their games after completing the course.", "et": "Kursuse läbija saab kõik põhiteadmised plaanipäraseks arvutimängude loomiseks (sh mängude psühholoogia, analüüs ja turustamine), oskuse luua mänguideedest praktilisi kavandeid ning neid projektina ellu viia. Kursuse käigus valmib õppijal arvutimängukavand ning koos tiimiga ka arvutimäng. \nKursusel osalejad saavad lektorilt ja ülikoolilt abi mänguloomise tiimide koostamisel, partnerite leidmisel ning oma mängude turustamisel pärast kursuse läbimist."}], "notes": {}}, "grading": {"independent_work": {"et": "Game design homeworks (given in lectures)\nTechnology homeworks (given in labs)\nMaking a game in a team (groups of 3) and presenting the milestone reports\nPeer review for another team's game\nPresenting the finished game at the end of the semester."}, "independent_work_assessments": [{"work_type": {"code": "homework", "et": "Kodutöö", "en": "home work"}, "description": {"et": "The homeworks have to be submitted in time and meet the criteria."}}, {"work_type": {"code": "project", "et": "Projekt", "en": "project"}, "description": {"et": "The project has to be submitted in time and meet the criteria."}}], "grade_preconditions": {"et": "Student has presented the game progress during the milestone presentations.\nStudent has collected at least 20 points from the lectures and labs (40 points total)."}, "grade_evaluation": {"et": "Attending to the game design lecture 10%\nGame design and technology homeworks 30%\nDeveloping and presenting the project 60%"}, "debt_elimination": {"et": "Project representation can be arranged with the teacher."}, "assessment_scale": {"code": "grade", "et": "Eristav (A, B, C, D, E, F, mi)", "en": "differentiated (A, B, C, D, E, F, not present)"}, "results_available_from": {}}, "resources": {"web_based": {"code": "2", "et": "põimõpe", "en": "blended learning"}, "website_url": "https://courses.cs.ut.ee", "is_moodle_connected": false}, "participants": {"lecturers": [{"person_uuid": "e581042b-6cfc-e4aa-944f-e3cea6e53350", "person_name": "Raimond-Hendrik Tunnel", "structural_unit": {"code": "LTAT05", "name": {"en": "Chair of Software Engineering", "et": "tarkvaratehnika õppetool"}, "level": 3, "academic": true, "supports_continuous_learning": false, "parent_code": "LTAT"}, "is_responsible": true, "is_teaching": false}, {"person_uuid": "02d2d03c-2c7f-84a5-dc2b-f949dc2e31d7", "person_name": "Jaanus Jaggo", "structural_unit": {"code": "LTAT05", "name": {"en": "Chair of Software Engineering", "et": "tarkvaratehnika õppetool"}, "level": 3, "academic": true, "supports_continuous